[31m-# Pure-Css-Components readme[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Generated on 2016-09-11 using[m
[31m-[generator-yeogurt@1.5.3](https://github.com/larsonjj/generator-yeogurt)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Description[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This is an example readme file.[m
[31m-Describe your site/app here.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Technologies used[m
[31m-[m
[31m-JavaScript[m
[31m-- [Browserify](http://browserify.org/) with ES6/2015 support through [Babel](https://babeljs.io/)[m
[31m-- [Node](https://nodejs.org/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Styles[m
[31m-- [Less](http://lesscss.org/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Markup[m
[31m-- [Jade](http://jade-lang.com/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Optimization[m
[31m-- [Imagemin](https://github.com/imagemin/imagemin)[m
[31m-- [Uglify](https://github.com/mishoo/UglifyJS)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Server[m
[31m-- [BrowserSync](http://www.browsersync.io/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Linting[m
[31m-- [ESlint](http://eslint.org/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Automation[m
[31m-- [Gulp](http://gulpjs.com)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Code Management[m
[31m-- [Editorconfig](http://editorconfig.org/)[m
[31m-- [Git](https://git-scm.com/)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Automated tasks[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This project uses [Gulp](http://gulpjs.com) to run automated tasks for development and production builds.[m
[31m-The tasks are as follows:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-`gulp --production`: Same as `gulp serve --production` also run `gulp test` and  not boot up production server[m
[31m-[m
[31m-`gulp serve`: Compiles preprocessors and boots up development server[m
[31m-`gulp serve --open`: Same as `gulp serve` but will also open up site/app in your default browser[m
[31m-`gulp serve --production`: Same as `gulp serve` but will run all production tasks so you can view the site/app in it's final optimized form[m
[31m-[m
[31m-`gulp test`: Lints all `*.js` file in the `source` folder using eslint[m
[31m-[m
[31m-***Adding the `--debug` option to any gulp task displays extra debugging information (ex. data being loaded into your templates)***[m
