[31m-#### Using Non-CommonJS modules with browserify-shim[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Sometimes you need to use libraries that attach themselves to the window object and don't work with browserify very well.[m
[31m-In this case, you can use a transform called [browserify-shim](https://github.com/thlorenz/browserify-shim).[m
[31m-[m
[31m-***Step 1: Install browserify-shim transform for browserify***[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Browserify doesn't support Non-CommonJS scripts out of the box (jQuery plugins, window.* libs, etc), but you can install a transform called 'browserify-shim' to remedy that:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-npm install --save-dev browserify-shim[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-***Step 2: Install desired npm package***[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Now you can install your desired npm package:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-// Example: jQuery plugin[m
[31m-[m
[31m-npm install --save slick-carousel[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-***Step 3: Setup browserify-shim***[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Add the following to your `package.json` file:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```json[m
[31m-"browserify": {[m
[31m-  "transform": [ "browserify-shim" ][m
[31m-},[m
[31m-"browser": {[m
[31m-  "slick-carousel": "./node_modules/slick-carousel/slick/slick.js"[m
[31m-},[m
[31m-"browserify-shim": {[m
[31m-  "slick-carousel": {[m
[31m-    "exports": null,[m
[31m-    "depends": "jquery:$"[m
[31m-  }[m
[31m-},[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-> Note: [slick-carousel](http://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/) requires jQuery, hence the `"depends": "jquery:$"`[m
[31m-[m
[31m-***Step 4: Import file to your project***[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Now you can include your desired module/lib within your `src/_scripts/main.js` file:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```js[m
[31m-// ES5[m
[31m-require('slick-carousel');[m
[31m-[m
[31m-// ES6[m
[31m-import 'slick-carousel';[m
[31m-[m
[31m-...[m
[31m-[m
[31m-$('#someId').slick(); // Activates slick plugin[m
[31m-```[m
